<doc id="1254834" wikidata="Q4809772" url="?curid=1254834" title="Savalan">
<text>Savalan is a village and municipality in the Qabala Rayon of Azerbaijan with a population of 294. Since 2007 the Savalan Valley, between the Turyanchay and Garachay rivers has given its name to a major new Azerbaijani wine with a new grape processing plant on the Agdash-Qabala road at nearby Qaradeyin.

